item.description: Explore More The Howard Hughes Corp., which operates the Seaport complex on South Street, is putting its money – a whopping $55 million — where its mouth is. Hughes just bought a 25 percent stake in Jean-Georges Restaurants (JGR), the 40-eatery empire of the great New York chef Jean-Georges Vongerichten. His local places include flagship Jean-Georges, Nougatine, The Fulton at the Seaport, ABC Kitchen, Jo-Jo and The Mark. On top of $45 million Hughes is paying for the minority stake, it also ponied up $10 million more for an option to buy 20 percent more of Vongerichten’s company.
